cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about video person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel graph representation learning scheme, which involves iterative feature propagation and regularization, indicating that it may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper utilizes pose alignment and feature affinity connections to construct the graph, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
